Compilation: 

        . PROBLEM: 
            . Importing header units didn't work with clang for me, if I try to import both iostream and 
                string like we did for this example with other compilers. The issue seems documented 
                here: https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/58540
            . Reverting to good old includes in the global module for this example with clang.
        . Commands: 

            //Compile the interface into pcm and the implementation into an object file
                . clang++ -std=c++20 -stdlib=libc++ -x c++-system-header iostream --precompile -o iostream.pcm
                . clang++ -std=c++20 -stdlib=libc++ -fmodule-file=iostream.pcm -x c++-module math.ixx --precompile -o math_stuff.pcm
                . clang++ -std=c++20 -stdlib=libc++ math_impl.cpp -fmodule-file=math_stuff=math_stuff.pcm -fmodule-file=iostream.pcm -c -o math_impl.o

            //Generate the object of the entry point file
                . clang++ -std=c++20 -stdlib=libc++ -fmodule-file=iostream.pcm main.cpp -fprebuilt-module-path=. -c -o main.o

            //Generate the object file from the pcm files you generated. Be mindful of the dependencies
                . clang++ -std=c++20 -stdlib=libc++ -fmodule-file=iostream.pcm math_stuff.pcm -c -o math_stuff.o


            //Pull everything together.
                . clang++ -std=c++20 -stdlib=libc++ main.o math_stuff.o  math_impl.o -o rooster
               
